  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You can make use of a torch as a deadly, macelike weapon.</em><br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>You treat a torch as a light weapon that deals bludgeoning damage equal to that of a light mace of its size plus 1 point of fire damage, and you do not incur penalties as you would for using it as an improvised weapon.<br/><br/><b>Normal</b><br/>A torch used in combat is treated as a one-handed improvised weapon that deals bludgeoning damage equal to that of a gauntlet of its size plus 1 point of fire damage.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>By spending 2 stamina points when you hit an opponent with a torch, you can increase the amount of fire damage dealt by the torch to 1d4.",
